<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id9088f729-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5203"><num value="5203">§ 5203.</num><heading> Enforcement</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9088f72a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5203/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Attorney General</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General shall take the necessary steps and institute the necessary legal action to effectuate the policies and provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9088f72b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5203/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Relief</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any district court of the United States for a district in which a violation of this chapter occurs shall have authority, upon petition of relief by the Attorney General, to grant injunctive and such other equitable relief as it shall deem necessary to enforce the provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id9088f72c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/204/tX/s1004">Pub. L. 100–204, title X, § 1004</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1407">101 Stat. 1407</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
